Public Domain

This work is in the public domain in the United States because it consists of
material created by agencies of the United States government.

The original Digital DATCOM software was developed by the United States Air 
Force (USAF) at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base using public funds and is
therefore in the public domain.

Any modifications, enhancements, or modern implementations in this repository
are also released into the public domain to preserve the open nature of these
heritage aerospace algorithms.

The mathematical foundations of aerospace engineering should be free and
accessible to all.

